---
layout: base.njk
title: Resources and publications
eyebrow: Resources and publications
heading: Shared <em>knowledge</em>
lead: News, publications and outreach materials on the health and welfare of camelids.
description: "News, publications and outreach materials on the health and welfare of camelids by Camelid Research Studies APS."
permalink: /en/risorse/
---
<section class="bg-soft">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">News</div>
    <h2>Latest <em>news</em></h2>
    {% set articoliEn = collections.news_en | reverse %}
    {% set articoliIt = collections.news | reverse %}
    {% if articoliEn | length %}
    <div class="rows">
      {% for a in articoliEn %}
      <a class="row" href="{{ a.url }}">
        <span class="meta">{{ a.date | dataIt }}</span>
        <span class="title">{{ a.data.title }}{% if a.data.sommario %}<small>{{ a.data.sommario }}</small>{% endif %}</span>
        <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% elif articoliIt | length %}
    <p class="empty-note" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">Our news articles are currently published in Italian only.</p>
    <div class="rows">
      {% for a in articoliIt %}
      <a class="row" href="{{ a.url }}">
        <span class="meta">{{ a.date | dataIt }}</span>
        <span class="title">{{ a.data.title }}{% if a.data.sommario %}<small>{{ a.data.sommario }}</small>{% endif %}</span>
        <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="empty-note">No news has been published yet. The first updates will come with the launch of the 2026&ndash;2027 projects.</div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bg-white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">Camelid Research Library</div>
    <h2>Scientific <em>library</em></h2>
    <p class="lead">Evidence-based summaries of scientific studies on camelids &mdash; reviewed and commented by the association. Each card summarises the objectives, methods, results and clinical implications of a published article.</p>
    {% set schedeEn = collections.biblioteca_en | reverse %}
    {% set schedeIt = collections.biblioteca | reverse %}
    {% set schede = schedeEn if schedeEn | length else schedeIt %}
    {% if schede | length %}
    <div class="bib-index">
      {% for s in schede %}
      <a class="bib-index-card" href="{{ s.url }}">
        <span class="bib-index-code">{{ s.data.code }}</span>
        <div class="bib-index-body">
          <h3>{{ s.data.title }}</h3>
          <div class="bib-index-meta">{{ s.data.authors }} &middot; {{ s.data.journal }}, {{ s.data.year }}</div>
          {% if s.data.area %}<span class="bib-index-area">{{ s.data.area }}</span>{% endif %}
        </div>
        <span class="bib-index-arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="empty-note">The first cards of the Camelid Research Library are being prepared. Each card is reviewed by the association&rsquo;s scientific team and will be published here once completed.</div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bg-soft">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">Deep dives</div>
    <h2>Outreach <em>materials</em></h2>
    <p class="lead">Informative articles on alpacas and llamas, based on scientific sources and curated by the association.</p>
    {% set apprEn = collections.divulgazione_en | reverse %}
    {% set apprIt = collections.divulgazione | reverse %}
    {% if apprEn | length %}
    <div class="rows">
      {% for a in apprEn %}
      <a class="row" href="{{ a.url }}">
        <span class="meta">{{ a.date | dataIt }}</span>
        <span class="title">{{ a.data.title }}{% if a.data.sommario %}<small>{{ a.data.sommario }}</small>{% endif %}</span>
        <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% elif apprIt | length %}
    <p class="empty-note" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">Our outreach articles are currently published in Italian only.</p>
    <div class="rows">
      {% for a in apprIt %}
      <a class="row" href="{{ a.url }}">
        <span class="meta">{{ a.date | dataIt }}</span>
        <span class="title">{{ a.data.title }}{% if a.data.sommario %}<small>{{ a.data.sommario }}</small>{% endif %}</span>
        <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="empty-note">The association is newly established: the first publications and outreach materials will arrive with the launch of the 2026&ndash;2027 projects.</div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>
